data.name: CareGave Health Corp
data.headline: On demand medical staffing platform
data.summary:
CareGave Health fills clinical open shifts for healthcare clients. We connect local health facilities with skilled doctors, nurses, and physical therapists with little to no agency costs. Receive on-demand professional help at hospitals, nursing homes, physician practices, rehab centers, and other medical facilities.

Our Purpose:
To simplify the healthcare staffing industry. CareGave serves as a partner for healthcare facilities to cover open shifts for nurses, locum tenens doctors, and physical therapists.

CareGave works with all medical facilities that use temporary healthcare workers. With CareGave, hospitals, nursing homes, rehab centers, and other healthcare facilities can hire trained healthcare workers on a per diem basis or temp basis. Clinicians and employers connect directly online or via an application, bypassing hefty recruiter and agency fees. This helps reduce the cost and increase the efficiency of filling critical clinical jobs.

Bounties allow CodeAlly community members to get paid when successfully referring their friends or getting hired.
For employers, this system provides a way to promote their jobs without risk. They either hire developers, or the service is free.

Key differentiators:
Referral network within a job board
 Success-based job advertising
Over 1000 developers join weekly, just 8 months after the launch

data.name: Willog
data.headline: Innovative, Industry's only, Item-level Condition Monitoring Solution
data.summary:
As a fast-growing startup, Willog provides a “item-level condition monitoring solution” that innovates the supply chain of sensitive, perishable or valuable goods where condition monitoring is required, and its efforts are to create a transparent and connected logistics flow. Based on its patented sensor technology and its cloud-based software, Willog helps companies gain seamless visibility down to the item-level and control over their shipments across their supply chain so they can have condition foresights and insights to improve their bottom line.

As of May 2021, Willog acquired 25 enterprise customers including MNCs like Hyundai Motor Group and DHL Express within a year. Willog is rapidly expanding its presence in various industries including bio-pharmaceutical, fresh food, and special logistics, where condition monitoring is key to business continuity. Going forward, while strengthening its leadership position in Korea, Willog will accelerate global expansion with partnerships in America, Kazakhstan, and Malaysia.
